# resume-preparation environment. Copy to .env and adjust. .env is gitignored.
#
# PREFERRED: put model settings in `secrets/secrets.env` instead (copy it from
# secrets/secrets.env.example). The CLIs and web app load that file automatically,
# it supports the hosted-server aliases LLAMA_SERVER_URL / API_KEY, and
# `npm run secrets:check` shows what's loaded. This .env is an alternative for
# `node --env-file=.env ...`.

# ---- LLM endpoint (local model OR a llama server over the web) ----
# Any OpenAI-compatible chat-completions server (llama.cpp llama-server, Ollama,
# vLLM, ...). The app pins temperature 0 + a fixed seed for reproducible reviews.
# Local example:  http://localhost:11434/v1  (Ollama)  /  http://localhost:8080/v1 (llama.cpp)
# Hosted example: https://your-llama-server.example.com/v1
LLM_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434/v1
# A hosted server's URL can also be given as LLAMA_SERVER_URL (mapped to LLM_BASE_URL).
# LLAMA_SERVER_URL=https://your-llama-server.example.com/v1
# Model tag the server serves. "local" works for single-model llama-server.
LLM_MODEL=llama3.1:8b
# Bearer token, only if the server was started with --api-key. Leave unset for an
# open local endpoint. (Alias: API_KEY.)
# LLM_API_KEY=your-secret-key
# Request tuning (all optional).
# LLM_SEED=0
# LLM_MAX_TOKENS=2048
# LLM_TIMEOUT_MS=120000

# ---- Storage ----
# Root directory for the app-level snapshot store (documents, versions, diffs,
# reviews). Local-first; gitignored. See DESIGN.md, "Versioning".
DATA_DIR=.data

# ---- LinkedIn assisted fill (OPTIONAL, OFF BY DEFAULT) ----
# When "true", enables the browser-assisted LinkedIn field-fill flow. This drives
# your logged-in browser and may conflict with LinkedIn's User Agreement / risk
# account limits. Leave false to use copy-paste-ready text + instructions only.
LINKEDIN_ASSISTED_FILL=false
